Date: 2/26/2025

Fee: No Fee

Point of Contact: The Brink Team
Location: 5998 Alcala Park, Knauss School of Business, Nexus Theater - Ground Floor, San Diego CA 92110-8001

Training Topics: Business Financing
Description:
 

BRINK PITCH PREP FOR SDAC: PITCH DECONSTRUCTION

COURSE DESCRIPTION

Brink Pitch Prep for SDAC is a weekly series running January to February 2025 to help entrepreneurs prepare to compete in the San Diego Angel Conference (SDAC). SDAC, hosted by San Diego State University (SDSU), is a 3-month series of events (March to May 2025) that seeks to fund founders by activating angel investors who raise funds to invest in the winner of the pitch competition. Through a series of evaluations and pitch events, investors arrive at 6 finalists who pitch at the SDAC finale on June 5, 2025. The SDAC application deadline is February 27, 2025. 

Event Format

Pitch Deconstruction is a popular Brink event that allows entrepreneurs to practice their pitch in front of an audience and hear feedback and advice from SDAC investors. It's a great way to get visibility, introductions, and practice. Here’s how it works: Founders line up and present their 1-minute pitch to SDAC investors and the audience. SDAC investors give overall feedback. All attendees vote on their favorites. The presenters with the top 3-5 votes come back and deliver a 3-minute pitch with slides and where they get 1:1 feedback from SDAC investors that we all can learn from. Come prepared to pitch! Pizza, soda, and a bottle refill station provided.

What to expect: 

Present your 1-minute pitch
Hear what’s trending among entrepreneurial startups
Be prepared to present a 3-minute pitch with slides
Hear advice and best practices from SDAC investors

About Event
​Join us for a Department of Navy SBIR Info Session!  

​Learn everything you need to know about SBIR funding in this engaging and informative workshop. Offered in partnership with The Brink SBDC, the Office of Innovation and Commercialization (OIC) at UC San Diego, and Connect, this session is tailored for small businesses, entrepreneurs, and researchers who are starting—or considering starting—an innovative company and are exploring various funding sources.  

​During this webinar, you’ll hear from:  

​A Navy SBIR Program Manager providing insights into DoN SBIR opportunities and processes.  

​A successful small business who has navigated and thrived in DoD SBIR programs.  

​An experienced grant-writing advisor sharing practical tips to help you craft compelling proposals.  

​Come prepared to learn, ask questions, and leave ready to explore funding opportunities and start writing your proposal. No prior experience or knowledge is required.

​11:00 AM – Welcome & Introduction - Gretel von Son (5 min)

Description:
Business Startup Power Hour

COURSE DESCRIPTION

Join us for our Business Startup Power Hour in English and in Spanish, where aspiring entrepreneurs and new business owners can drop in, ask questions, and receive personalized advice on how to successfully launch and grow their business. Whether you're in the early stages of planning or ready to take the next step, this event is designed to provide you with the guidance and support you need to succeed.

What to Expect:

Expert Guidance: Receive personalized advice from experienced business mentors on key aspects of starting and growing a business, including business planning, funding, marketing, and more.
Networking Opportunities: Connect with other aspiring business owners, share experiences, and build valuable relationships that can help you navigate the entrepreneurial journey.
Actionable Insights: Walk away with clear, actionable steps to move your business forward, whether you're refining your business plan, exploring funding options, or planning your marketing strategy.
 

Hora de poder para emprendedores

DESCRIPTION DEL CURSO

Hora de poder para emprendedores: Únete a nuestra hora de poder para emprendedores en inglés y en español, donde aspirantes a emprendedores y nuevos dueños de negocios pueden participar, hacer preguntas y recibir asesoramiento personalizado sobre cómo lanzar y hacer crecer su negocio con éxito. Ya sea que estés en las primeras etapas de planificación o listo para dar el siguiente paso, este evento está diseñado para brindarte la orientación y el apoyo que necesitas para tener éxito.

Puntos clave:

Orientación experta: Recibe asesoramiento personalizado de mentores empresariales experimentados sobre aspectos clave para iniciar y hacer crecer un negocio, incluyendo la planificación empresarial, financiamiento, marketing y más.
Oportunidades de networking: Conéctate con otros aspirantes a dueños de negocios, comparte experiencias y construye relaciones valiosas que te ayudarán a navegar el camino del emprendimiento.
Ideas accionables: Sal del evento con pasos claros y accionables para avanzar tu negocio, ya sea que estés refinando tu plan de negocios, explorando opciones de financiamiento o planificando tu estrategia de marketing.
